ent CYP450 3A4 inhibitor, a progressive dosage reduction may be required over a longer period if the corticosteroid is to be withdrawn from therapy, as there may be a significant risk of adrenal suppression.', 'Metabolism', 'The possibility of increased corticosteroid effects should be considered during coadministration with potent and moderate CYP450 3A4 inhibitors.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/72785/', '', 'Mometasone furoate, Fluorometholone, Mometasone furoate, Amcinonide, Fluocinolone acetonide, Hydrocortisone butyrate, Fluocinonide, Fluorometholone, Clobetasol, Beclomethasone dipropionate, Salicylic acid, More', 'Lamivudine, Paritaprevir, Glecaprevir, Tenofovir alafenamide, Maraviroc, Simeprevir, Cabotegravir, Valaciclovir, Zanamivir, Lenacapavir, Velpatasvir, More', 1767369485);
